messages.messageBody:
>>Can you send me a link to that site (if you still know it)? Tamzin would
love to do that. We've googled and didn't come up >>with much.<<

Here is the link that Hannah used that lets you mess around with colors in
rooms. It's a little complicated, but if you read everything carefully on
each page, you eventually end up with a palette of colors that you want to
work with (and you can easily change), and then it gives you the sample room
of your choice to click on, and then you can manipulate the parts of the
room and make them the colors that you want.

http://www.behr.com/behrx/workbook/

Have fun!

Jacki
